verses.text_plain: Moreover the Lord answered Job, and said,
verses.verse_html: 1Moreover the Lord answered Job, and said,

verses.text_plain: Shall he that contendeth with the Almighty instruct him? he that reproveth God, let him answer it.
verses.verse_html: 2Shall he that contendeth with the Almighty instruct him? he that reproveth God, let him answer it.

verses.text_plain: Then Job answered the Lord, and said,
verses.verse_html: 3Then Job answered the Lord, and said,

verses.text_plain: Behold, I am vile; what shall I answer thee? I will lay mine hand upon my mouth.
verses.verse_html: 4Behold, I am vile; what shall I answer thee? I will lay mine hand upon my mouth.

verses.text_plain: Once have I spoken; but I will not answer: yea, twice; but I will proceed no further.
verses.verse_html: 5Once have I spoken; but I will not answer: yea, twice; but I will proceed no further.

tokens.text: but I will proceed no further

verses.text_plain: Then answered the Lord unto Job out of the whirlwind, and said,
verses.verse_html: 6Then answered the Lord unto Job out of the whirlwind, and said,

verses.text_plain: Gird up thy loins now like a man: I will demand of thee, and declare thou unto me.
verses.verse_html: 7Gird up thy loins now like a man: I will demand of thee, and declare thou unto me.

verses.text_plain: Wilt thou also disannul my judgment? wilt thou condemn me, that thou mayest be righteous?
verses.verse_html: 8Wilt thou also disannul my judgment? wilt thou condemn me, that thou mayest be righteous?

tokens.text: me, that thou mayest be righteous

verses.text_plain: Hast thou an arm like God? or canst thou thunder with a voice like him?
verses.verse_html: 9Hast thou an arm like God? or canst thou thunder with a voice like him?

verses.text_plain: Deck thyself now with majesty and excellency; and array thyself with glory and beauty.
verses.verse_html: 10Deck thyself now with majesty and excellency; and array thyself with glory and beauty.

verses.text_plain: Cast abroad the rage of thy wrath: and behold every one that is proud, and abase him.
verses.verse_html: 11Cast abroad the rage of thy wrath: and behold every one that is proud, and abase him.

verses.text_plain: Look on every one that is proud, and bring him low; and tread down the wicked in their place.
verses.verse_html: 12Look on every one that is proud, and bring him low; and tread down the wicked in their place.

verses.text_plain: Hide them in the dust together; and bind their faces in secret.
verses.verse_html: 13Hide them in the dust together; and bind their faces in secret.

verses.text_plain: Then will I also confess unto thee that thine own right hand can save thee.
verses.verse_html: 14Then will I also confess unto thee that thine own right hand can save thee.

tokens.text: unto thee that thine own right hand

verses.text_plain: Behold now behemoth, which I made with thee; he eateth grass as an ox.
verses.verse_html:
15Behold now behemoth, which I made with thee; he eateth grass as an ox.
 behemoth: probably an extinct animal of some kind

tokens.text: probably an extinct animal of some kind

footnotes.body_text: behemoth: probably an extinct animal of some kind
footnotes.body_html: behemoth: probably an extinct animal of some kind

verses.text_plain: Lo now, his strength is in his loins, and his force is in the navel of his belly.
verses.verse_html: 16Lo now, his strength is in his loins, and his force is in the navel of his belly.

verses.text_plain: He moveth his tail like a cedar: the sinews of his stones are wrapped together.
verses.verse_html:
17He moveth his tail like a cedar: the sinews of his stones are wrapped together.
 He: or, He setteth up

footnotes.body_html: He: or, He setteth up

verses.text_plain: His bones are as strong pieces of brass; his bones are like bars of iron.
verses.verse_html: 18His bones are as strong pieces of brass; his bones are like bars of iron.

verses.text_plain: He is the chief of the ways of God: he that made him can make his sword to approach unto him.
verses.verse_html: 19He is the chief of the ways of God: he that made him can make his sword to approach unto him.

verses.text_plain: Surely the mountains bring him forth food, where all the beasts of the field play.
verses.verse_html: 20Surely the mountains bring him forth food, where all the beasts of the field play.

verses.text_plain: He lieth under the shady trees, in the covert of the reed, and fens.
verses.verse_html: 21He lieth under the shady trees, in the covert of the reed, and fens.

verses.text_plain: The shady trees cover him with their shadow; the willows of the brook compass him about.
verses.verse_html: 22The shady trees cover him with their shadow; the willows of the brook compass him about.

verses.text_plain: Behold, he drinketh up a river, and hasteth not: he trusteth that he can draw up Jordan into his mouth.
verses.verse_html:
23Behold, he drinketh up a river, and hasteth not: he trusteth that he can draw up Jordan into his mouth.
 he drinketh up: Heb. he oppresseth

footnotes.body_text: he drinketh up: Heb. he oppresseth
footnotes.body_html: he drinketh up: Heb. he oppresseth

verses.text_plain: He taketh it with his eyes: his nose pierceth through snares.
verses.verse_html:
24He taketh it with his eyes: his nose pierceth through snares.
 He: or, Will any take him in his sight, or, bore his nose with a gin?

footnotes.body_text: He: or, Will any take him in his sight, or, bore his nose with a gin?
footnotes.body_html: He: or, Will any take him in his sight, or, bore his nose with a gin?
